    public enum LogLevel

    LogLevel - The logger level, used to indicate the log types.
    Author:
    AlienIdeology
    See Also:
    Logger, LogMode

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      DEBUG
      Log level: [DEBUG] Fine amount of messages, used to track internal events and debug.
      ERROR
      Log level: [ERROR] Used to indicate an user end error.
      FETAL
      Log level: [FETAL] Used to indicate a internal api error.
      INFO
      Log level: [INFO] Default log level, used to present important messages.
      TRACE
      Log level: [TRACE] Finest amount of messages, log everything possible.
      WARN
      Log level: [WARN] Used to warn the user, error related.
